# Gherkin Integration Gate

All agent-delivered functionality must be backed by executable Gherkin.

## Requirements

- Define or update at least one `features/**/*.feature` scenario for each behavior change.
- Tag scenarios for traceability from capability/feature IDs to scenario IDs.
- Keep step definitions executable (no pending/undefined steps).

## Completion signal

Do not mark an integration as completed unless this command passes:

`npm run integration:check`

## Validation expectations

- Failing or missing Gherkin scenarios means the change is not complete.
- If a change is internal/refactor-only, preserve or update existing scenarios to prove behavior parity.
